# shared-foundation — Project Rules (Index)

This repository uses **Cursor rules** under `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` for maintainable, scoped guidance.

Keep this file short. **Prefer extending an existing `.mdc` in the same domain** (e.g. Kotlin syntax → `kotlin-style.mdc`) instead of adding many tiny one-topic files; add a **new** `.mdc` when the topic is a new area (KDoc, tests, serialization contracts, …).

## Core principles (always on)

- **Precedence:** project rules in this repo override conflicting Cursor User Rules. What matters for contributors is under `.cursor/rules/` (committed), not personal global rules.
- This is a **Kotlin Multiplatform library**: **shared wire types and constants** (HTTP/WebSocket JSON DTOs, route path strings, header/field names, machine-readable **error code** strings, password policy contracts) for **backend and client**. Not an app: **no UI**, **no Ktor `Application`/`HttpClient` wiring** here (consumers: [README.md](README.md)).
- **FQN in Kotlin code is forbidden**: do not write fully qualified names in expressions/type annotations/generics; use imports (or typealiases). Only keep minimal FQN when imports are impossible/ambiguous, and explain the reason in PR/commit message.
- Never suggest or run tests automatically after test changes.

## What this library actually contains (summary)

- **`core/common`:** `FoundationJson`; `ApiErrorResponse`; `CommonErrorCodes` / `CommonErrorArgs`; WebSocket (`SocketFrame`, payloads, `WebSocketContract`); `CommonApiFields` / `CommonHttpHeaders`; shared domain bits (e.g. `UserClientType`); validation **annotations** (`RequiredField`, …).
- **`core/security`:** `SecurityErrorCodes` / `SecurityErrorArgs`; security settings HTTP models/routes; **password policy** (`PasswordPolicy`, `PasswordPolicyValidator`, sealed `PasswordPolicyValidatorResult`).
- **`core/settings`:** global settings HTTP models/routes and contracts.
- **`feature/user`:** `UserErrorCodes` / `UserErrorArgs`; user/session/auth HTTP contracts; user **domain** enums/sealed types (roles, providers, statuses).
- **Published alignment:** `bom` module.

## Detailed rules live in `.cursor/rules/`

- `project-overview.mdc` — identity, stack, module layout, Gradle boundaries, consumer repos.
- `architecture-patterns.mdc` — serialization, **HTTP routes** (method + `Request body` / `Response body` **only** when this module defines that DTO; no “none” placeholder lines), WebSocket, **API error DTO + error code objects**, validation annotations, password policy.
- `docs-kdoc-basics.mdc` + `docs-kdoc-type-requirements.mdc` — **mandatory** KDoc (package/path doc: definition of done in `docs-kdoc-basics.mdc`, including **every public interface member** unless scope is narrowed).
- `testing-style.mdc` — test conventions (if/when tests exist).
- `kotlin-style.mdc` — `when` subject / naming, `if`+`return` braces.
- `ai-workflow.mdc` — dependencies, modules, no test runs, consumer compatibility.

## Not in this repository

- **Compose / UI / `composeResources`** — client apps and KMP SDK handle those; not applicable to cursor rules here beyond “do not add them.”
